To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Cambodia, you have a few transportation options depending on your preference and availability:

1. Walking: The distance of 1km is very walkable, and it will take approximately 10-15 minutes to reach the grocery store on foot. This can be a good option if you enjoy walking and want to explore the local surroundings.

2. Bicycle: If you have access to a bicycle, it can be a convenient and eco-friendly way to reach the grocery store. Bicycles are common in Cambodia, and many areas have bicycle lanes or bike-friendly roads.

3. Tuk-tuk: Tuk-tuks are a popular mode of transport in Cambodia. They are small, three-wheeled vehicles that can accommodate several passengers. You can easily find tuk-tuks by the roadside or near popular gathering spots, and they are relatively affordable for short distances. Negotiate the fare with the driver before hopping in.

4. Motorcycle taxi (motodop): Similar to tuk-tuks, motorcycle taxis, locally known as motodops, are a common means of transportation in Cambodia. You can find motodops near most street corners and popular areas. Negotiate the fare before hopping on, and make sure to wear a helmet for safety.
